title: Washington DC Meetup This Tuesday
summary:
Key ideas:
- Meetup event organized by Scott is happening on September 24 in Washington DC
- The event features special guests Georgia Ray, Alex Tabarrok, and a few people from MIRI and EA organizations
- Anyone is welcome to attend, regardless of their status as a "typical SSC reader"
- Updates on location will be posted in a Google Group

Key learnings:
- Meetup events are a great way to meet new people and connect with others who share similar interests
- Even if you feel awkward, it's worth attending events like these to expand your social circle and gain new perspectives

Key questions:
- How can we make sure that everyone feels welcome and included at events like these?
- What can we do to encourage more people to attend community events and connect with others who share similar goals?
